                <h3 class="my-3">Need for Drug Disposal</h3>
                <p>
                    Prescription of more opioid drug result in leftover pills that are available for diversion and inappropirate drug use. According to multiple studies, excessive opioid drugs prescribed for all surgical and emergency visits for pain. This excessive presciption may result large amount of drug leftover for diversion. The presence of higher quantity prescription associated with more patient request for opioid drugs. Among those who abuse opioid drug, more than 70% obtain via diversion, and other 40 - 50% receive from family and friend leftover.
                    Carlos A Pino (MD). 2019. Prescription of opioids for Acute Pain in Opioid Naive Patients: Scott Fishman (MD) and Marianna Croley (MD), eds.
                </p>
